tOriginal) => ...)` as workaround вЂ” adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-9\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters вЂ” fragile to reordering by future contributors.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-10\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-11\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-12\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` вЂ” if tarpaulin outputs `\\\"coverage\\\": \\\"85.5\\\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-13\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects вЂ” unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-14\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) вЂ” caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-15\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**Time constraint:** Verification not started вЂ” insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-16\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-17\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\",\n      \"source\": \"retro\",\n      \"resolved\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"migrated-18\",\n      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"**[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected вЂ” container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\",\n 