{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WBSnkMFf2dDh3aR7p9qViG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Story 8.5: Rust Dockerfile template generation\n     2в†’\n     3в†’Status: verifying\n     4в†’\n     5в†’<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6в†’\n     7в†’## Story\n     8в†’\n     9в†’As a developer deploying a Rust project,\n    10в†’I want codeharness to generate a multi-stage Dockerfile,\n    11в†’so that I get a minimal runtime image with just the compiled binary.\n    12в†’\n    13в†’## Acceptance Criteria\n    14в†’\n    15в†’1. **AC1:** Given a Rust project (stack = `'rust'`) without a Dockerfile, when `generateDockerfileTemplate('/project', 'rust')` is called, then it writes a Dockerfile and returns `ok({ path: '/project/Dockerfile', stack: 'rust' })` вЂ” NOT `'generic'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16в†’2. **AC2:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then it contains a multi-stage build: a `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder` stage and a `FROM debian:bookworm-slim` runtime stage <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17в†’3. **AC3:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then the builder stage includes `cargo build --release` and the runtime stage uses `COPY --from=builder` to copy the compiled binary <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18в†’4. **AC4:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then the runtime stage installs `curl` and `jq` via `apt-get install`, runs as a non-root user, and includes `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*` cache cleanup <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19в†’5. **AC5:** Given a Rust project with an existing Dockerfile, when `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is called, then it returns `fail('Dockerfile already exists')` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20в†’6. **AC6:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile, when `validateDockerfile()` is called against it, then it passes all 6 rule categories with zero gaps <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21в†’7. **AC7:** Given `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project without a Dockerfile, when the Dockerfile template generation phase executes, then it generates a Rust-specific Dockerfile (not generic) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    22в†’\n    23в†’## Tasks / Subtasks\n    24в†’\n    25в†’- [x] Task 1: Add `rustTemplate()` function to `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n    26в†’  - [x]1.1 Create `rustTemplate(): string` returning a multi-stage Dockerfile string\n    27в†’  - [x]1.2 Builder stage: `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder`, `WORKDIR /build`, `COPY . .`, `RUN cargo build --release`\n    28в†’  - [x]1.3 Runtime stage: `FROM debian:bookworm-slim`, `apt-get install curl jq`, `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `COPY --from=builder /build/target/release/myapp /usr/local/bin/myapp`, `USER nobody`, `WORKDIR /workspace`\n    29в†’  - [x]1.4 Include inline section comments matching existing template style\n    30в†’- [x] Task 2: Add `'rust'` branch to `generateDockerfileTemplate()` (AC: #1)\n    31в†’  - [x]2.1 In the if/else chain (lines 99-108), add `else if (stack === 'rust')` BEFORE the generic fallthrough\n    32в†’  - [x]2.2 Set `content = rustTemplate()` and `resolvedStack = 'rust'`\n    33в†’- [x] Task 3: Update existing test that asserts `'rust'` maps to `'generic'` (AC: #1)\n    34в†’  - [x]3.1 In `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` line 167, the test `'generates generic Dockerfile when stack is unknown'` passes `'rust'` and expects `stack: 'generic'` вЂ” this MUST change\n    35в†’  - [x]3.2 Replace `'rust'` in that test with a different unknown stack (e.g., `'java'`) so the generic fallthrough test still works\n    36в†’- [x] Task 4: Add new `describe('generateDockerfileTemplate вЂ” rust')` test block (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n    37в†’  - [x]4.1 Test: returns `stack: 'rust'` and correct path\n    38в†’  - [x]4.2 Test: contains `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder` and `FROM debian:bookworm-slim`\n    39в†’  - [x]4.3 Test: includes `cargo build --release` in builder stage\n    40в†’  - [x]4.4 Test: includes `COPY --from=builder` to copy compiled binary\n    41в†’  - [x]4.5 Test: includes `curl` and `jq` verification tools\n    42в†’  - [x]4.6 Test: includes `USER nobody` for non-root execution\n    43в†’  - [x]4.7 Test: includes apt cache cleanup (`rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`)\n    44в†’  - [x]4.8 Test: includes inline section comments (`# Build`, `# System utilities`, `# Install`, `# Run as non-root`)\n    45в†’- [x] Task 5: Add Rust template to validation compliance tests (AC: #6)\n    46в†’  - [x]5.1 In the `describe('generated Dockerfiles pass validateDockerfile()')` block (line 273), add a `'rust template passes all 6 rule categories'` test\n    47в†’  - [x]5.2 Generate Rust template, feed content to `validateDockerfile()` via mocked `readFileSync`, assert `passed: true` and `gaps: []`\n    48в†’- [x] Task 6: Run full test suite вЂ” zero regressions\n    49в†’\n    50в†’## Dev Notes\n    51в†’\n    52в†’### Current Code Structure\n    53в†’\n    54в†’`src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (119 lines) has three template functions and one generator:\n    55в†’- `nodejsTemplate()` L21 в†’ single-stage, `FROM node:22-slim`, `npm install -g` from tarball\n    56в†’- `pythonTemplate()` L41 в†’ single-stage, `FROM python:3.12-slim`, `pip install` from wheel\n    57в†’- `genericTemplate()` L59 в†’ single-stage, `FROM node:22-slim`, placeholder\n    58в†’- `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` L82 в†’ if/else chain: `'nodejs'` в†’ `'python'` в†’ else (generic)\n    59в†’\n    60в†’Currently `'rust'` falls through to the `else` branch and produces a generic Dockerfile. After this story, it gets its own dedicated multi-stage template.\n    61в†’\n    62в†’### Multi-Stage Build вЂ” Why Different\n    63в†’\n    64в†’Existing templates (nodejs, python) are single-stage because they install from pre-built artifacts (tarball, wheel). Rust compiles from source to a static binary вЂ” the builder stage is needed to compile, then only the binary is copied to a minimal runtime image. This is standard Rust Docker practice.\n    65в†’\n    66в†’### Validator Compatibility Analysis (AC6)\n    67в†’\n    68в†’The 6 rule categories in `dockerfile-validator.ts` and how the Rust template passes:\n    69в†’\n    70в†’1. **pinned-from** (L71): Checks all `FROM` lines for version tags. Both `rust:1.82-slim` and `debian:bookworm-slim` have version tags. **PASSES.**\n    71в†’2. **binary-on-path** (L85): Regex `/COPY\\s+--from=/i` at L90 matches `COPY --from=builder ...`. **PASSES.**\n    72в†’3. **verification-tools** (L97): Looks for `curl` and `jq` on `apt-get install` lines. **PASSES.**\n    73в†’4. **no-source-copy** (L116): Regex checks for `COPY src/`, `COPY lib/`, `COPY test/`. **CRITICAL**: The builder stage uses `COPY . .` which does NOT match these patterns. Do NOT use `COPY src/ src/` in the builder stage вЂ” it triggers the validator. Use `COPY . .` instead. **PASSES with `COPY . .`.**\n    74в†’5. **non-root-user** (L129): Checks for `USER` instruction with non-root user. `USER nobody` qualifies. **PASSES.**\n    75в†’6. **cache-cleanup** (L144): Checks for `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/`. **PASSES.**\n    76в†’\n    77в†’### Template Content\n    78в†’\n    79в†’```dockerfile\n    80в†’# === Builder stage ===\n    81в†’FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder\n    82в†’\n    83в†’WORKDIR /build\n    84в†’\n    85в†’# Copy project files\n    86в†’COPY . .\n    87в†’\n    88в†’# Build release binary\n    89в†’RUN cargo build --release\n    90в†’\n    91в†’# === Runtime stage ===\n    92в†’FROM debian:bookworm-slim\n    93в†’\n    94в†’# System utilities for verification\n    95в†’RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    96в†’\n    97в†’# Install compiled binary from builder (update 'myapp' to your binary name)\n    98в†’COPY --from=builder /build/target/release/myapp /usr/local/bin/myapp\n    99в†’\n   100в†’# Run as non-root user\n   101в†’USER nobody\n   102в†’\n   103в†’WORKDIR /workspace\n   104в†’```\n   105в†’\n   106в†’The binary name `myapp` is a placeholder вЂ” same approach as `genericTemplate()` using `placeholder`. Users edit it. Do NOT attempt to read `Cargo.toml` at generation time.\n   107в†’\n   108в†’### Breaking Test at Line 167\n   109в†’\n   110в†’The existing test at line 164-172:\n   111в†’```typescript\n   112в†’it('generates generic Dockerfile when stack is unknown', () => {\n   113в†’    mockExistsSync.mockReturnValue(false);\n   114в†’    const r = generateDockerfileTemplate('/project', 'rust');\n   115в†’    expect(r.success).toBe(true);\n   116в†’    if (r.success) {\n   117в†’      expect(r.data.stack).toBe('generic');\n   118в†’    }\n   119в†’  });\n   120в†’```\n   121в†’\n   122в†’This test uses `'rust'` as the \"unknown stack\" example. After adding the Rust branch, this breaks. **Fix**: Replace `'rust'` with `'java'` (or any other unsupported stack) in this test, and create a separate Rust-specific test block.\n   123в†’\n   124в†’### init-project.ts Integration (AC7)\n   125в†’\n   126в†’`init-project.ts` line 78 already calls `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)`. When `detectStack()` returns `'rust'`, the generator now produces the Rust template. No changes to `init-project.ts` needed.\n   127в†’\n   128в†’### Architecture Constraints\n   129в†’\n   130в†’- **<300 line limit**: Adding ~30 lines to 119-line file = ~149 lines. Safe.\n   131в†’- **No new npm dependencies**: Pure string template.\n   132в†’- **NFR5**: Uses existing `Result<T>`, `DockerfileTemplateResult` type. No type changes.\n   133в†’\n   134в†’### Project Structure Notes\n   135в†’\n   136в†’Files to modify:\n   137в†’- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` вЂ” add `rustTemplate()` + branch\n   138в†’- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` вЂ” update generic test, add rust test block + validation test\n   139в†’\n   140в†’Files for reference only (do NOT modify):\n   141в†’- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` вЂ” validator rules\n   142в†’- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` вЂ” calls generator (no changes needed)\n   143в†’- `src/modules/infra/index.ts` вЂ” re-exports (no changes needed)\n   144в†’\n   145в†’### References\n   146в†’\n   147в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts#L82-118 вЂ” generateDockerfileTemplate function with if/else chain]\n   148в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts#L21-74 вЂ” existing template functions pattern]\n   149в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts#L164-172 вЂ” existing test mapping rustв†’generic (MUST UPDATE)]\n   150в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts#L271-333 вЂ” validation compliance test block (ADD RUST)]\n   151в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts#L86-95 вЂ” checkBinaryOnPath accepts COPY --from=]\n   152в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts#L116-127 вЂ” checkNoSourceCopy regex (avoid COPY src/)]\n   153в†’- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts#L78 вЂ” generateDockerfileTemplate called during init]\n   154в†’- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#FR4 вЂ” requirement]\n   155в†’\n   156в†’### Previous Story Intelligence (8-4)\n   157в†’\n   158в†’- 8-4 added cargo-tarpaulin to dependency registry. Zero regressions on ~2980 tests.\n   159в†’- 8-4 only touched `deps.ts` and `deps.test.ts` вЂ” no file overlap with this story.\n   160в†’- Mocking pattern in dockerfile-template tests uses `vi.mock('node:fs')` at top level with `vi.mocked()` вЂ” follow this exact pattern.\n   161в†’\n   162в†’### Git Intelligence\n   163в†’\n   164в†’Recent commits: 4e805b9 (8-4 verified), ebaddac (8-3 verified), d6a76bf (8-2 verified), 4c7f498 (8-1 detection).\n   165в†’All Rust stories so far modified: `stack-detect.ts`, `state.ts`, `coverage.ts`, `deps.ts` + tests.\n   166в†’This story touches only `dockerfile-template.ts` and its test вЂ” clean isolation from previous work.\n   167в†’\n   168в†’### Do NOT Duplicate\n   169в†’\n   170в†’- Story 4-2 created `dockerfile-template.ts` with nodejs/python/generic. This story EXTENDS it.\n   171в†’- Story 8-6 will create `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` (verification Dockerfile). Do NOT create verification templates here.\n   172в†’\n   173в†’<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   174в†’## Verification Requirements\n   175в†’\n   176в†’- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.proof.md`)\n   177в†’- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   178в†’- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   179в†’\n   180в†’## Documentation Requirements\n   181в†’\n   182в†’- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   183в†’- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.md`\n   184в†’\n   185в†’## Testing Requirements\n   186в†’\n   187в†’- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   188в†’- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   189в†’- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   190в†’<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   191в†’\n   192в†’## Dev Agent Record\n   193в†’\n   194в†’### Agent Model Used\n   195в†’\n   196в†’Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   197в†’\n   198в†’### Debug Log References\n   199в†’\n   200в†’None.\n   201в†’\n   202в†’### Completion Notes List\n   203в†’\n   204в†’- All 6 tasks completed. 34/34 dockerfile-template tests pass.\n   205в†’- 1 pre-existing failure in migration.test.ts (unrelated to this story).\n   206в†’- Zero regressions: 2994/2995 tests pass across full suite.\n   207в†’\n   208в†’### File List\n   209в†’\n   210в†’- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` вЂ” added `rustTemplate()` function and `'rust'` branch in if/else chain\n   211в†’- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` вЂ” fixed generic test (rustв†’java), added 8 Rust tests, added Rust validation compliance test\n   212в†’- `src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md` вЂ” updated dockerfile-template.ts entry to include rust (review fix)\n   213в†’- `docs/exec-plans/active/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.proof.md` вЂ” showboat proof document (review fix)\n   214в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MpYJycPJfk2nBuCCAUW85g","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"eb942ae5-6099-4880-9754-af0252471a8b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:08:58.602Z"}
