{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FKV3erwrt8EjR6t9LGnoMu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Story 8-6: Rust Verification Dockerfile\n     2в†’\n     3в†’## Status: backlog\n     4в†’\n     5в†’## Story\n     6в†’\n     7в†’As a developer verifying a Rust project,\n     8в†’I want a verification environment with Rust tooling, Semgrep, and showboat,\n     9в†’So that automated verification works for Rust projects.\n    10в†’\n    11в†’## Acceptance Criteria\n    12в†’\n    13в†’- [ ] AC1: Given `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` exists, when built, then it includes `rust:1.82-slim`, Python + Semgrep, showboat, cargo-tarpaulin, curl, jq <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14в†’- [ ] AC2: Given the verification Dockerfile, when inspected, then OTLP environment variables are configured pointing to host Docker endpoint <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15в†’\n    16в†’## Technical Notes\n    17в†’\n    18в†’### Verification Dockerfile\n    19в†’\n    20в†’File: `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` (new file).\n    21в†’\n    22в†’Follow the pattern of the existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` (Node.js verification Dockerfile) but replace Node.js tooling with Rust tooling.\n    23в†’\n    24в†’**Base image:** `rust:1.82-slim`\n    25в†’\n    26в†’**Required tools to install:**\n    27в†’- Python 3 + pipx (needed for Semgrep вЂ” Semgrep requires Python even in Rust projects)\n    28в†’- Semgrep via `pipx install semgrep && pipx ensurepath`\n    29в†’- showboat (proof document generator)\n    30в†’- `cargo-tarpaulin` via `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin`\n    31в†’- `curl` and `jq` (for verification scripts)\n    32в†’\n    33в†’**OTLP environment variables:**\n    34в†’```dockerfile\n    35в†’ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318\n    36в†’ENV OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=codeharness-verify\n    37в†’```\n    38в†’\n    39в†’**Structure:**\n    40в†’```dockerfile\n    41в†’FROM rust:1.82-slim\n    42в†’\n    43в†’# Install system deps\n    44в†’RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    45в†’    python3 python3-pip python3-venv pipx curl jq git \\\n    46в†’    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    47в†’\n    48в†’# Install Python tools (Semgrep, showboat)\n    49в†’RUN pipx install semgrep && pipx ensurepath\n    50в†’RUN pipx install showboat && pipx ensurepath\n    51в†’\n    52в†’# Install Rust tools\n    53в†’RUN cargo install cargo-tarpaulin\n    54в†’\n    55в†’# OTLP config\n    56в†’ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318\n    57в†’ENV OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=codeharness-verify\n    58в†’\n    59в†’WORKDIR /workspace\n    60в†’```\n    61в†’\n    62в†’### Reference\n    63в†’\n    64в†’- `templates/Dockerfile.verify` вЂ” Existing Node.js verification Dockerfile (pattern to follow)\n    65в†’- The analyzer module (`src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`) auto-discovers Semgrep rules вЂ” no code changes needed\n    66в†’\n    67в†’### No Code Changes\n    68в†’\n    69в†’This story is a pure template file creation. No TypeScript source changes needed. The verification system already supports custom Dockerfiles per stack вЂ” this file is discovered by convention.\n    70в†’\n    71в†’## Files to Change\n    72в†’\n    73в†’- `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` (new) вЂ” Create Rust verification Dockerfile with rust:1.82-slim base, Python + Semgrep, showboat, cargo-tarpaulin, curl, jq, and OTLP env vars\n    74в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MpYJycPJfk2nBuCCAUW85g","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"ffad0d5b-597e-4f9f-bd4b-080113b5486f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:09:19.599Z"}
