{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q9KoH9ZvdgfBrL4hrjpeXc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’---\n     2в†’title: 'Full Rust Stack Support'\n     3в†’slug: 'rust-stack-support'\n     4в†’created: '2026-03-23'\n     5в†’status: 'ready-for-dev'\n     6в†’stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n     7в†’tech_stack: ['typescript', 'rust', 'vitest', 'semgrep']\n     8в†’files_to_modify:\n     9в†’  - src/lib/stack-detect.ts\n    10в†’  - src/lib/otlp.ts\n    11в†’  - src/lib/coverage.ts\n    12в†’  - src/lib/state.ts\n    13в†’  - src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts\n    14в†’  - src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts\n    15в†’  - src/commands/init.ts\n    16в†’  - src/modules/infra/init-project.ts\n    17в†’  - src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts\n    18в†’  - src/lib/deps.ts\n    19в†’files_to_create:\n    20в†’  - templates/otlp/rust.md\n    21в†’  - templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    22в†’  - patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml\n    23в†’  - patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml\n    24в†’  - patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml\n    25в†’code_patterns:\n    26в†’  - 'if/else on stack === \"nodejs\" | \"python\" вЂ” add \"rust\" branch at each'\n    27в†’  - 'Per-stack install/patch/detect functions: installNodeOtlp(), installPythonOtlp() в†’ add installRustOtlp()'\n    28в†’  - 'Cargo.toml TOML parsing for app type and dependency detection'\n    29в†’test_patterns:\n    30в†’  - 'Mirror existing stack-detect.test.ts patterns for Rust cases'\n    31в†’  - 'Mirror otlp.test.ts patterns with Cargo.toml fixtures'\n    32в†’  - 'Mirror coverage.test.ts patterns with tarpaulin JSON fixtures'\n    33в†’---\n    34в†’\n    35в†’# Tech-Spec: Full Rust Stack Support\n    36в†’\n    37в†’**Created:** 2026-03-23\n    38в†’\n    39в†’## Overview\n    40в†’\n    41в†’### Problem Statement\n    42в†’\n    43в†’Codeharness supports Node.js and Python across stack detection, OTLP instrumentation, coverage tools, Dockerfile generation, Semgrep rules, and docs scaffolding. Rust projects get `null` stack and no harness features. ~25 language-conditional code paths need Rust branches.\n    44в†’\n    45в†’### Solution\n    46в†’\n    47в†’Add Rust as a first-class stack at parity with TypeScript/Python. Use `cargo-tarpaulin` for coverage, `opentelemetry`/`opentelemetry-otlp` crates for OTLP, basic scaffolding + LLM guidance for instrumentation, and Semgrep Rust rules for observability static analysis. Treat workspaces (`[workspace]`) as single projects.\n    48в†’\n    49в†’### Scope\n    50в†’\n    51в†’**In Scope:**\n    52в†’- Stack detection (`Cargo.toml`, `[workspace]` support)\n    53в†’- App type detection (CLI/library/server via Cargo.toml parsing)\n    54в†’- Dockerfile generation (`rustTemplate()`)\n    55в†’- Verification Dockerfile (`Dockerfile.verify.rust`)\n    56в†’- OTLP dependency addition + config + LLM guidance docs\n    57в†’- Coverage tool detection (`cargo-tarpaulin`)\n    58в†’- Coverage report parsing (tarpaulin JSON format)\n    59в†’- Semgrep rules for Rust observability patterns\n    60в†’- Docs scaffolding (AGENTS.md, build commands)\n    61в†’- State file support (`rust` stack, `cargo-tarpaulin` tool)\n    62в†’- Tests for all new code paths\n    63в†’\n    64в†’**Out of Scope:**\n    65в†’- Full auto-instrumentation code generation (LLM handles this via guidance docs)\n    66в†’- Per-crate workspace enumeration (treat workspace as single project)\n    67в†’- New observability backends\n    68в†’- Custom verification strategies\n    69в†’\n    70в†’## Context for Development\n    71в†’\n    72в†’### Codebase Patterns\n    73в†’\n    74в†’- All stack-conditional logic uses `if (stack === 'nodejs') { ... } else if (stack === 'python') { ... }` вЂ” add `else if (stack === 'rust') { ... }` at each location\n    75в†’- Per-stack functions follow naming convention: `installNodeOtlp()`, `installPythonOtlp()` в†’ add `installRustOtlp()`\n    76в†’- Coverage detection follows: `detectNodeCoverageTool()`, `detectPythonCoverageTool()` в†’ add `detectRustCoverageTool()`\n    77в†’- Dockerfile templates follow: `nodejsTemplate()`, `pythonTemplate()` в†’ add `rustTemplate()`\n    78в†’- OTLP templates are static markdown files in `templates/otlp/{stack}.md`\n    79в†’- Tests mirror source structure: `src/lib/__tests__/`, `src/modules/infra/__tests__/`\n    80в†’\n    81в†’### Files to Reference\n    82в†’\n    83в†’| File | Purpose | Lines | Rust Touchpoints |\n    84в†’| ---- | ------- | ----- | ---------------- |\n    85в†’| `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | Stack detection + app type detection | 146 | `detectStack()` L7-14, `detectAppType()` L72-145, add Rust dep constants |\n    86в†’| `src/lib/otlp.ts` | OTLP instrumentation per stack | ~330 | `installRustOtlp()` new fn, `instrumentProject()` L295, `configureOtlpEnvVars()` L258-274, `configureAgent()` L207-227 |\n    87в†’| `src/lib/coverage.ts` | Coverage tool detection + report parsing | ~400 | `detectCoverageTool()` L35-53, `detectRustCoverageTool()` new fn, `parseTarpaulinCoverage()` new fn, `parseCoverageReport()` L257, `parseTestCounts()` L308 add cargo test format, `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union |\n    88в†’| `src/lib/state.ts` | HarnessState interface | вЂ” | `coverage.tool` type, `otlp.rust_env_hint` field |\n    89в†’| `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | Dockerfile generation per stack | 119 | `rustTemplate()` new fn, `generateDockerfileTemplate()` L99-108 |\n    90в†’| `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | AGENTS.md + docs generation | 197 | `getStackLabel()` L32-36, `getCoverageTool()` L38-41, `generateAgentsMdContent()` L43-98 |\n    91в†’| `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` | Semgrep static analysis runner | ~150 | No code changes вЂ” Semgrep auto-discovers `.yaml` rules by language |\n    92в†’| `src/lib/deps.ts` | Dependency registry | ~100 | Add `cargo-tarpaulin` to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` |\n    93в†’| `patches/observability/*.yaml` | Semgrep rules (JS/TS) | 3 files | Create 3 new Rust-specific YAML rules |\n    94в†’| `templates/otlp/nodejs.md` | Node.js OTLP guide | 54 | Pattern for `templates/otlp/rust.md` |\n    95в†’| `templates/otlp/python.md` | Python OTLP guide | 52 | Pattern for `templates/otlp/rust.md` |\n    96в†’| `templates/Dockerfile.verify` | Node.js verification Dockerfile | вЂ” | Pattern for `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` |\n    97в†’\n    98в†’### Technical Decisions\n    99в†’\n   100в†’- **Cargo.toml parsing:** Use `readTextSafe()` (already in stack-detect.ts) + simple string matching / regex on TOML content. No TOML parser dependency. Check for `[workspace]`, `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`, and known framework deps in `[dependencies]`."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MpYJycPJfk2nBuCCAUW85g","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"c98e4d09-3d41-4996-b622-d06c254f876d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:09:20.492Z"}
