{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DMENhhRZPLfxw5e67xcJHi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’---\n     2в†’stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n     3в†’inputDocuments:\n     4в†’  - prd-operational-excellence.md\n     5в†’  - architecture-overhaul.md\n     6в†’  - product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md\n     7в†’workflowType: 'architecture'\n     8в†’project_name: 'codeharness'\n     9в†’user_name: 'BMad'\n    10в†’date: '2026-03-19'\n    11в†’---\n    12в†’\n    13в†’# Architecture Decision Document вЂ” Operational Excellence\n    14в†’\n    15в†’_Extends the overhaul architecture (architecture-overhaul.md) with observability analysis, audit, and infrastructure validation capabilities._\n    16в†’\n    17в†’## Project Context Analysis\n    18в†’\n    19в†’### Requirements Overview\n    20в†’\n    21в†’28 FRs across 5 capability areas:\n    22в†’- **Observability Static Analysis (FR1-5):** Source scanning, log coverage, gap detection\n    23в†’- **Observability Runtime Validation (FR6-9):** Test telemetry verification, gap detection\n    24в†’- **Observability Coverage Metric (FR10-12):** Metric computation, enforcement, tracking\n    25в†’- **Audit Command (FR13-21):** Comprehensive compliance check, story generation\n    26в†’- **Infrastructure Guidelines (FR22-25):** Dockerfile rules, validation, templates\n    27в†’- **Workflow Enforcement (FR26-28):** Integration with dev/review workflows\n    28в†’\n    29в†’### How This Extends the Overhaul Architecture\n    30в†’\n    31в†’The overhaul established 5 modules: infra, sprint, verify, dev, review. This sprint adds:\n    32в†’- **New module: `observability/`** вЂ” static analysis, runtime validation, coverage metric\n    33в†’- **Expanded module: `audit/`** вЂ” replaces onboard, uses observability module + existing checks\n    34в†’- **Extended: `infra/`** вЂ” Dockerfile guidelines and validation\n    35в†’- **Extended: `patches/`** вЂ” observability enforcement rules for dev/review\n    36в†’\n    37в†’### Technical Constraints\n    38в†’\n    39в†’- Existing Result<T> pattern applies to all new functions\n    40в†’- Module boundary rules from overhaul apply (index.ts exports only, no circular imports)\n    41в†’- Atomic write pattern for state updates\n    42в†’- <300 line file limit\n    43в†’- Must work with both VictoriaMetrics and OpenSearch backends (ObservabilityBackend interface)\n    44в†’\n    45в†’### Research Inputs\n    46в†’\n    47в†’Technical research (2026-03-19) established:\n    48в†’- No industry-standard observability coverage metric exists вЂ” report static and runtime separately\n    49в†’- Semgrep is the right static analysis tool вЂ” YAML rules, `pattern-not-inside` detects absence of logging\n    50в†’- Analyzer interface allows tool flexibility вЂ” harness cares about gap report format, not which tool produces it\n    51в†’- Runtime validation matches test coverage paths to telemetry events by module/service, not line-level\n    52в†’\n    53в†’## Starter: N/A (Brownfield)\n    54в†’\n    55в†’All technology decisions preserved from overhaul architecture. New dependencies: Semgrep (static analysis tool, installed as project dev dependency).\n    56в†’\n    57в†’## Core Architectural Decisions\n    58в†’\n    59в†’### Decision 1: Static Analysis via Configurable Analyzer (Not Custom AST)\n    60в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MpYJycPJfk2nBuCCAUW85g","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"a33db238-d368-45fc-903f-add50782fac6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:09:34.066Z"}
