{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SHnMyCwkVTNwEcSpVjod6E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’<workflow>\n     2в†’  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3в†’  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4в†’  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5в†’  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6в†’  <critical>Only modify the story file in these areas: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record (Debug Log, Completion Notes), File List,\n     7в†’    Change Log, and Status</critical>\n     8в†’  <critical>Execute ALL steps in exact order; do NOT skip steps</critical>\n     9в†’  <critical>Absolutely DO NOT stop because of \"milestones\", \"significant progress\", or \"session boundaries\". Continue in a single execution\n    10в†’    until the story is COMPLETE (all ACs satisfied and all tasks/subtasks checked) UNLESS a HALT condition is triggered or the USER gives\n    11в†’    other instruction.</critical>\n    12в†’  <critical>Do NOT schedule a \"next session\" or request review pauses unless a HALT condition applies. Only Step 6 decides completion.</critical>\n    13в†’  <critical>User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not code updates.</critical>\n    14в†’\n    15в†’  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Find next ready story and load it\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n    16в†’    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided\">\n    17в†’      <action>Use {{story_path}} directly</action>\n    18в†’      <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    19в†’      <action>Extract story_key from filename or metadata</action>\n    20в†’      <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    21в†’    </check>\n    22в†’\n    23в†’    <!-- Sprint-based story discovery -->\n    24в†’    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n    25в†’      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE sprint-status.yaml file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n    26в†’      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n    27в†’      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n    28в†’      <action>Parse the development_status section completely to understand story order</action>\n    29в†’\n    30в†’      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n    31в†’        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    32в†’        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n    33в†’        - Status value equals \"ready-for-dev\"\n    34в†’      </action>\n    35в†’\n    36в†’      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev or in-progress story found\">\n    37в†’        <output>рџ“‹ No ready-for-dev stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n    38в†’\n    39в†’          **Current Sprint Status:** {{sprint_status_summary}}\n    40в†’\n    41в†’          **What would you like to do?**\n    42в†’          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    43в†’          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories before development (recommended quality check)\n    44в†’          3. Specify a particular story file to develop (provide full path)\n    45в†’          4. Check {{sprint_status}} file to see current sprint status\n    46в†’\n    47в†’          рџ’Ў **Tip:** Stories in `ready-for-dev` may not have been validated. Consider running `validate-create-story` first for a quality\n    48в†’          check.\n    49в†’        </output>\n    50в†’        <ask>Choose option [1], [2], [3], or [4], or specify story file path:</ask>\n    51в†’\n    52в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    53в†’          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    54в†’        </check>\n    55в†’\n    56в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n    57в†’          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n    58в†’        </check>\n    59в†’\n    60в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n    61в†’          <ask>Provide the story file path to develop:</ask>\n    62в†’          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    63в†’          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    64в†’        </check>\n    65в†’\n    66в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '4'\">\n    67в†’          <output>Loading {{sprint_status}} for detailed status review...</output>\n    68в†’          <action>Display detailed sprint status analysis</action>\n    69в†’          <action>HALT - User can review sprint status and provide story path</action>\n    70в†’        </check>\n    71в†’\n    72в†’        <check if=\"user provides story file path\">\n    73в†’          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    74в†’          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    75в†’        </check>\n    76в†’      </check>\n    77в†’    </check>\n    78в†’\n    79в†’    <!-- Non-sprint story discovery -->\n    80в†’    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n    81в†’      <action>Search {implementation_artifacts} for stories directly</action>\n    82в†’      <action>Find stories with \"ready-for-dev\" status in files</action>\n    83в†’      <action>Look for story files matching pattern: *-*-*.md</action>\n    84в†’      <action>Read each candidate story file to check Status section</action>\n    85в†’\n    86в†’      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev stories found in story files\">\n    87в†’        <output>рџ“‹ No ready-for-dev stories found\n    88в†’\n    89в†’          **Available Options:**\n    90в†’          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    91в†’          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories\n    92в†’          3. Specify which story to develop\n    93в†’        </output>\n    94в†’        <ask>What would you like to do? Choose option [1], [2], or [3]:</ask>\n    95в†’\n    96в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    97в†’          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    98в†’        </check>\n    99в†’\n   100в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n   101в†’          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n   102в†’        </check>\n   103в†’\n   104в†’        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n   105в†’          <ask>It's unclear what story you want developed. Please provide the full path to the story file:</ask>\n   106в†’          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n   107в†’          <action>Continue with provided story file</action>\n   108в†’        </check>\n   109в†’      </check>\n   110в†’\n   111в†’      <check if=\"ready-for-dev story found in files\">\n   112в†’        <action>Use discovered story file and extract story_key</action>\n   113в†’      </check>\n   114в†’    </check>\n   115в†’\n   116в†’    <action>Store the found story_key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\") for later status updates</action>\n   117в†’    <action>Find matching story file in {implementation_artifacts} using story_key pattern: {{story_key}}.md</action>\n   118в†’    <action>Read COMPLETE story file from discovered path</action>\n   119в†’\n   120в†’    <anchor id=\"task_check\" />\n   121в†’\n   122в†’    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   123в†’\n   124в†’    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   125в†’    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   126в†’    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   127в†’\n   128в†’    <action>Identify first incomplete task (unchecked [ ]) in Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   129в†’\n   130в†’    <action if=\"no incomplete tasks\">\n   131в†’      <goto step=\"6\">Completion sequence</goto>\n   132в†’    </action>\n   133в†’    <action if=\"story file inaccessible\">HALT: \"Cannot develop story without access to story file\"</action>\n   134в†’    <action if=\"incomplete task or subtask requirements ambiguous\">ASK user to clarify or HALT</action>\n   135в†’  </step>\n   136в†’\n   137в†’  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load project context and story information\">\n   138в†’    <critical>Load all available context to inform implementation</critical>\n   139в†’\n   140в†’    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards and project-wide patterns (if exists)</action>\n   141в†’    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   142в†’    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   143в†’    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   144в†’    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   145в†’    <output>вњ… **Context Loaded**\n   146в†’      Story and project context available for implementation\n   147в†’    </output>\n   148в†’  </step>\n   149в†’\n   150в†’  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Detect review continuation and extract review context\">\n   151в†’    <critical>Determine if this is a fresh start or continuation after code review</critical>\n   152в†’\n   153в†’    <action>Check if \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section exists in the story file</action>\n   154в†’    <action>Check if \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection exists under Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   155в†’\n   156в†’    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section exists\">\n   157в†’      <action>Set review_continuation = true</action>\n   158в†’      <action>Extract from \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section:\n   159в†’        - Review outcome (Approve/Changes Requested/Blocked)\n   160в†’        - Review date\n   161в†’        - Total action items with checkboxes (count checked vs unchecked)\n   162в†’        - Severity breakdown (High/Med/Low counts)\n   163в†’      </action>\n   164в†’      <action>Count unchecked [ ] review follow-up tasks in \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection</action>\n   165в†’      <action>Store list of unchecked review items as {{pending_review_items}}</action>\n   166в†’\n   167в†’      <output>вЏЇпёЏ **Resuming Story After Code Review** ({{review_date}})\n   168в†’\n   169в†’        **Review Outcome:** {{review_outcome}}\n   170в†’        **Action Items:** {{unchecked_review_count}} remaining to address\n   171в†’        **Priorities:** {{high_count}} High, {{med_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   172в†’\n   173в†’        **Strategy:** Will prioritize review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) before continuing with regular tasks.\n   174в†’      </output>\n   175в†’    </check>\n   176в†’\n   177в†’    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section does NOT exist\">\n   178в†’      <action>Set review_continuation = false</action>\n   179в†’      <action>Set {{pending_review_items}} = empty</action>\n   180в†’\n   181в†’      <output>рџљЂ **Starting Fresh Implementation**\n   182в†’\n   183в†’        Story: {{story_key}}\n   184в†’        Story Status: {{current_status}}\n   185в†’        First incomplete task: {{first_task_description}}\n   186в†’      </output>\n   187в†’    </check>\n   188в†’  </step>\n   189в†’\n   190в†’  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Mark story in-progress\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   191в†’    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n   192в†’      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   193в†’      <action>Read all development_status entries to find {{story_key}}