{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EMgb6RjcpUzTFc7WZDt7kd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’<workflow>\n     2в†’  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3в†’  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4в†’  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5в†’  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6в†’\n     7в†’  <critical>рџ”Ґ YOU ARE AN ADVERSARIAL CODE REVIEWER - Find what's wrong or missing! рџ”Ґ</critical>\n     8в†’  <critical>Your purpose: Validate story file claims against actual implementation</critical>\n     9в†’  <critical>Challenge everything: Are tasks marked [x] actually done? Are ACs really implemented?</critical>\n    10в†’  <critical>Find 3-10 specific issues in every review minimum - no lazy \"looks good\" reviews - YOU are so much better than the dev agent\n    11в†’    that wrote this slop</critical>\n    12в†’  <critical>Read EVERY file in the File List - verify implementation against story requirements</critical>\n    13в†’  <critical>Tasks marked complete but not done = CRITICAL finding</critical>\n    14в†’  <critical>Acceptance Criteria not implemented = HIGH severity finding</critical>\n    15в†’  <critical>Do not review files that are not part of the application's source code. Always exclude the _bmad/ and _bmad-output/ folders from the review. Always exclude IDE and CLI configuration folders like .cursor/ and .windsurf/ and .claude/</critical>\n    16в†’\n    17в†’\n    18в†’  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Load story and discover changes\">\n    19в†’    <action>Use provided {{story_path}} or ask user which story file to review</action>\n    20в†’    <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    21в†’    <action>Set {{story_key}} = extracted key from filename (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication.md\" в†’ \"1-2-user-authentication\") or story\n    22в†’      metadata</action>\n    23в†’    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Agent Record в†’ File List, Change Log</action>\n    24в†’\n    25в†’    <!-- Discover actual changes via git -->\n    26в†’    <action>Check if git repository detected in current directory</action>\n    27в†’    <check if=\"git repository exists\">\n    28в†’      <action>Run `git status --porcelain` to find uncommitted changes</action>\n    29в†’      <action>Run `git diff --name-only` to see modified files</action>\n    30в†’      <action>Run `git diff --cached --name-only` to see staged files</action>\n    31в†’      <action>Compile list of actually changed files from git output</action>\n    32в†’    </check>\n    33в†’\n    34в†’    <!-- Cross-reference story File List vs git reality -->\n    35в†’    <action>Compare story's Dev Agent Record в†’ File List with actual git changes</action>\n    36в†’    <action>Note discrepancies:\n    37в†’      - Files in git but not in story File List\n    38в†’      - Files in story File List but no git changes\n    39в†’      - Missing documentation of what was actually changed\n    40в†’    </action>\n    41в†’\n    42в†’    <invoke-protocol name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n    43в†’    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards (if exists)</action>\n    44в†’  </step>\n    45в†’\n    46в†’  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Build review attack plan\">\n    47в†’    <action>Extract ALL Acceptance Criteria from story</action>\n    48в†’    <action>Extract ALL Tasks/Subtasks with completion status ([x] vs [ ])</action>\n    49в†’    <action>From Dev Agent Record в†’ File List, compile list of claimed changes</action>\n    50в†’\n    51в†’    <action>Create review plan:\n    52в†’      1. **AC Validation**: Verify each AC is actually implemented\n    53в†’      2. **Task Audit**: Verify each [x] task is really done\n    54в†’      3. **Code Quality**: Security, performance, maintainability\n    55в†’      4. **Test Quality**: Real tests vs placeholder bullshit\n    56в†’    </action>\n    57в†’  </step>\n    58в†’\n    59в†’  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Execute adversarial review\">\n    60в†’    <critical>VALIDATE EVERY CLAIM - Check git reality vs story claims</critical>\n    61в†’\n    62в†’    <!-- Git vs Story Discrepancies -->\n    63в†’    <action>Review git vs story File List discrepancies:\n    64в†’      1. **Files changed but not in story File List** в†’ MEDIUM finding (incomplete documentation)\n    65в†’      2. **Story lists files but no git changes** в†’ HIGH finding (false claims)\n    66в†’      3. **Uncommitted changes not documented** в†’ MEDIUM finding (transparency issue)\n    67в†’    </action>\n    68в†’\n    69в†’    <!-- Use combined file list: story File List + git discovered files -->\n    70в†’    <action>Create comprehensive review file list from story File List and git changes</action>\n    71в†’\n    72в†’    <!-- AC Validation -->\n    73в†’    <action>For EACH Acceptance Criterion:\n    74в†’      1. Read the AC requirement\n    75в†’      2. Search implementation files for evidence\n    76в†’      3. Determine: IMPLEMENTED, PARTIAL, or MISSING\n    77в†’      4. If MISSING/PARTIAL в†’ HIGH SEVERITY finding\n    78в†’    </action>\n    79в†’\n    80в†’    <!-- Task Completion Audit -->\n    81в†’    <action>For EACH task marked [x]:\n    82в†’      1. Read the task description\n    83в†’      2. Search files for evidence it was actually done\n    84в†’      3. **CRITICAL**: If marked [x] but NOT DONE в†’ CRITICAL finding\n    85в†’      4. Record specific proof (file:line)\n    86в†’    </action>\n    87в†’\n    88в†’    <!-- Code Quality Deep Dive -->\n    89в†’    <action>For EACH file in comprehensive review list:\n    90в†’      1. **Security**: Look for injection risks, missing validation, auth issues\n    91в†’      2. **Performance**: N+1 queries, inefficient loops, missing caching\n    92в†’      3. **Error Handling**: Missing try/catch, poor error messages\n    93в†’      4. **Code Quality**: Complex functions, magic numbers, poor naming\n    94в†’      5. **Test Quality**: Are tests real assertions or placeholders?\n    95в†’    </action>\n    96в†’\n    97в†’    <check if=\"total_issues_found lt 3\">\n    98в†’      <critical>NOT LOOKING HARD ENOUGH - Find more problems!</critical>\n    99в†’      <action>Re-examine code for:\n   100в†’        - Edge cases and null handling\n   101в†’        - Architecture violations\n   102в†’        - Documentation gaps\n   103в†’        - Integration issues\n   104в†’        - Dependency problems\n   105в†’        - Git commit message quality (if applicable)\n   106в†’      </action>\n   107в†’      <action>Find at least 3 more specific, actionable issues</action>\n   108в†’    </check>\n   109в†’  </step>\n   110в†’\n   111в†’  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Present findings and fix them\">\n   112в†’    <action>Categorize findings: HIGH (must fix), MEDIUM (should fix), LOW (nice to fix)</action>\n   113в†’    <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   114в†’    <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   115в†’\n   116в†’    <output>**рџ”Ґ CODE REVIEW FINDINGS, {user_name}!**\n   117в†’\n   118в†’      **Story:** {{story_file}}\n   119в†’      **Git vs Story Discrepancies:** {{git_discrepancy_count}} found\n   120в†’      **Issues Found:** {{high_count}} High, {{medium_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   121в†’\n   122в†’      ## рџ”ґ CRITICAL ISSUES\n   123в†’      - Tasks marked [x] but not actually implemented\n   124в†’      - Acceptance Criteria not implemented\n   125в†’      - Story claims files changed but no git evidence\n   126в†’      - Security vulnerabilities\n   127в†’\n   128в†’      ## рџџЎ MEDIUM ISSUES\n   129в†’      - Files changed but not documented in story File List\n   130в†’      - Uncommitted changes not tracked\n   131в†’      - Performance problems\n   132в†’      - Poor test coverage/quality\n   133в†’      - Code maintainability issues\n   134в†’\n   135в†’      ## рџџў LOW ISSUES\n   136в†’      - Code style improvements\n   137в†’      - Documentation gaps\n   138в†’      - Git commit message quality\n   139в†’    </output>\n   140в†’\n   141в†’    <ask>What should I do with these issues?\n   142в†’\n   143в†’      1. **Fix them automatically** - I'll update the code and tests\n   144в†’      2. **Create action items** - Add to story Tasks/Subtasks for later\n   145в†’      3. **Show me details** - Deep dive into specific issues\n   146в†’\n   147в†’      Choose [1], [2], or specify which issue to examine:</ask>\n   148в†’\n   149в†’    <check if=\"user chooses 1\">\n   150в†’      <action>Fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues in the code</action>\n   151в†’      <action>Add/update tests as needed</action>\n   152в†’      <action>Update File List in story if files changed</action>\n   153в†’      <action>Update story Dev Agent Record with fixes applied</action>\n   154в†’      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = number of HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed</action>\n   155в†’      <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   156в†’    </check>\n   157в†’\n   158в†’    <check if=\"user chooses 2\">\n   159в†’      <action>Add \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection to Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   160в†’      <action>For each issue: `- [ ] [AI-Review][Severity] Description [file:line]`</action>\n   161в†’      <action>Set {{action_count}} = number of action items created</action>\n   162в†’      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   163в†’    </check>\n   164в†’\n   165в†’    <check if=\"user chooses 3\">\n   166в†’      <action>Show detailed explanation with code examples</action>\n   167в†’      <action>Return to fix decision</action>\n   168в†’    </check>\n   169в†’  </step>\n   170в†’\n   171в†’  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:review-enforcement -->\n   172в†’  <step n=\"4.5\" goal=\"Harness verification checks\">\n   173в†’    <critical>Codeharness requires these additional review checks</critical>\n   174в†’    <action>Verify Showboat proof document exists at docs/exec-plans/active/{{story_key}}.proof.md or docs/exec-plans/completed/{{story_key}}.proof.md</action>\n   175в†’    <action>Check AGENTS.md freshness вЂ” all modules in File List must have up-to-date AGENTS.md</action>\n   176в†’    <action>Verify test coverage meets 100% target for all changed modules</action>\n   177в†’    <action if=\"proof document missing\">Add HIGH finding: \"Missing Showboat proof document\"</action>\n   178в†’    <action if=\"AGENTS.md stale or missing for changed module\">Add MEDIUM finding: \"AGENTS.md missing or stale for {{module}}\"</action>\n   179в†’    <action if=\"coverage below target\">Add HIGH finding: \"Test coverage below 100% target\"</action>\n   180в†’  </step>\n   181в†’  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:review-enforcement -->\n   182в†’\n   183в†’  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Update story status and sync sprint tracking\">\n   184в†’    <!-- Determine new status based on review outcome -->\n   185в†’    <check if=\"all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed AND all ACs implemented\">\n   186в†’      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"done\"</action>\n   187в†’      <action>Update story Status field to \"done\"</action>\n   188в†’    </check>\n   189в†’    <check if=\"HIGH or MEDIUM issues remain OR ACs not fully implemented\">\n   190в†’      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   191в†’      <action>Update story Status field to \"in-progress\"</action>\n   192в†’    </check>\n   193в†’    <action>Save story file</action>\n   194в†’\n   195в†’    <!-- Determine sprint tracking status -->\n   196в†’    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n   197в†’      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"enabled\"</action>\n   198в†’    </check>\n   199в†’    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist\">\n   200в†’      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   201в†’    </check>\n   202в†’\n   203в†’    <!-- Sync sprint-status.yaml when story status changes (only if sprint tracking enabled) -->\n   204в†’    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   205в†’      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   206в†’      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   207в†’\n   208в†’      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'done'\">\n   209в†’        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"done\"</action>\n   210в†’        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   211в†’        <output>вњ… Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} в†’ done</output>\n   212в†’      </check>\n   213в†’\n   214в†’      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'in-progress'\">\n   215в†’        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   216в†’        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   217в†’        <output>рџ”„ Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} в†’ in-progress</output>\n   218в†’      </check>\n   219в†’\n   220в†’      <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   221в†’        <output>вљ пёЏ Story file updated, but sprint-status sync failed: {{story_key}} not found in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   222в†’      </check>\n   223в†’    </check>\n   224в†’\n   225в†’    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   226в†’      <output>в„№пёЏ Story status updated (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   227в†’    </check>\n   228в†’\n   229в†’    <output>**вњ… Review Complete!**\n   230в†’\n   231в†’      **Story Status:** {{new_status}}\n   232в†’      **Issues Fixed:** {{fixed_count}}\n   233в†’      **Action Items Created:** {{action_count}}\n   234в†’\n   235в†’      {{#if new_status == \"done\"}}Code review complete!{{else}}Address the action items and continue development.{{/if}}\n   236в†’    </output>\n   237в†’  </step>\n   238в†’\n   239в†’</workflow>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kg9tLGsBN5iJa4HVEh4QKa","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"bbc02144-56aa-46af-91d7-88abdc651bf0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:16:06.321Z"}
