{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kg9tLGsBN5iJa4HVEh4QKa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clean. All looks good.\n\n---\n\n**Review Complete**\n\n**Story:** 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 4 Medium, 1 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 4 Medium (all)\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. **MEDIUM вЂ” NFR9 violation (307 > 300 lines):** Merged `buildRustImage` and `buildGenericImage` into a single `buildSimpleImage(projectDir, variant, timeout?)` helper. env.ts now at 299 lines.\n2. **MEDIUM вЂ” Unreadable nested ternary in `resolveDockerfileTemplate`:** Replaced with a `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` lookup map. Extensible for future variants.\n3. **MEDIUM вЂ” Stale comment:** Updated hash-skip comment to mention Rust alongside generic and plugin.\n4. **MEDIUM вЂ” AGENTS.md stale:** Updated `src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md` to document Rust as a supported project type and include `detectProjectType` in exports.\n\n**Verification results:**\n- 2998 tests pass, zero regressions\n- 97% overall coverage (target: 90%)\n- All 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- None. All ACs correctly implemented; all tasks marked [x] verified against actual code.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Tests cast `'rust'` as `ReturnType<typeof detectStack>` (lines 674, 727, 747, 759) вЂ” unnecessary since `detectStack` returns `string | null`. Harmless but clutters test readability.\n- LOW: Missing Showboat proof document at `docs/exec-plans/active/8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile.proof.md`. This is a documentation gap that will be filled during the verification phase, not a code issue.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No direct test for `resolveDockerfileTemplate` with an unknown variant (e.g., `'java'`) вЂ” it falls through to `'Dockerfile.verify'` which is tested indirectly via the Node.js build path.\n- No test for `buildSimpleImage` timeout parameter propagation (Rust's 300s vs generic's default 120s). Would require inspecting the `execFileSync` call options in the mock.\n- AC7 (integration test for `codeharness init` on Rust project) is marked `integration-required` вЂ” not covered by unit tests, needs manual/integration verification.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The `buildSimpleImage` consolidation reduces duplication and keeps env.ts under the 300-line cap. The `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` map is extensible for future stack additions.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed; story advanced to `verifying`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa7f83319396c933f (use SendMessage with to: 'aa7f83319396c933f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58924\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 214926</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"261b0a89-7c57-4b12-b774-e5122f752ac5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:19:25.810Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile.md вЂ” perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions вЂ” proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY вЂ” End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupl