{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BHXX6UsMKp4TKfw4fxNyj2","type":"tool_result","content":"## Verification Complete\n\n**Results: 4 PASS, 3 FAIL, 1 ESCALATE**\n\n| AC | Status | Notes |\n|----|--------|-------|\n| AC1 | **FAIL** | `Dockerfile.verify.rust` not shipped in npm package |\n| AC2 | **FAIL** | Can't inspect OTLP vars вЂ” template file missing |\n| AC3 | **PASS** | Rust project detection works (`\"stack\":\"rust\"`) |\n| AC4 | **PASS** | Bundle routes rust to correct build function |\n| AC5 | **PASS** | `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` maps correctly |\n| AC6 | **PASS** | `\"rust\"` is valid project type in all code paths |\n| AC7 | **FAIL** | No Docker-in-Docker + template not shipped |\n| AC8 | **ESCALATE** | No source code in container for npm test |\n\n### Critical Bug\n\n**`package.json` `files` array is missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`** (and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`). The code logic is correct вЂ” detection, routing, and template resolution all work. But the actual Dockerfile template is never included in the npm package, so `resolveDockerfileTemplate(\"rust\")` will throw at runtime.\n\n**Fix:** Add `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` and `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic\"` to the `files` array in `package.json`.\n\nProof document written to `verification/8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile-proof.md`.\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"2427de17-73f6-496f-b04b-825cf55111e9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:24:30.259Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"## Verification Complete\n\n**Results: 4 PASS, 3 FAIL, 1 ESCALATE**\n\n| AC | Status | Notes |\n|----|--------|-------|\n| AC1 | **FAIL** | `Dockerfile.verify.rust` not shipped in npm package |\n| AC2 | **FAIL** | Can't inspect OTLP vars вЂ” template file missing |\n| AC3 | **PASS** | Rust project detection works (`\"stack\":\"rust\"`) |\n| AC4 | **PASS** | Bundle routes rust to correct build function |\n| AC5 | **PASS** | `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` maps correctly |\n| AC6 | **PASS** | `\"rust\"` is valid project type in all code paths |\n| AC7 | **FAIL** | No Docker-in-Docker + template not shipped |\n| AC8 | **ESCALATE** | No source code in container for npm test |\n\n### Critical Bug\n\n**`package.json` `files` array is missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`** (and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`). The code logic is correct вЂ” detection, routing, and template resolution all work. But the actual Dockerfile template is never included in the npm package, so `resolveDockerfileTemplate(\"rust\")` will throw at runtime.\n\n**Fix:** Add `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` and `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic\"` to the `files` array in `package.json`.\n\nProof document written to `verification/8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile-proof.md`.","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
