{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UFr73JyKjzUabCKBK1auri","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Story 8.6: Rust Verification Dockerfile вЂ” Verification Proof\n     2в†’\n     3в†’**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n     4в†’**Date:** 2026-03-23\n     5в†’**Container:** codeharness-verify (codeharness v0.23.1)\n     6в†’\n     7в†’---\n     8в†’\n     9в†’## AC1: Dockerfile.verify.rust template content\n    10в†’\n    11в†’**Status: [FAIL]**\n    12в†’\n    13в†’The `Dockerfile.verify.rust` template file is **not shipped** in the npm package. The `package.json` `files` field only includes `templates/Dockerfile.verify` вЂ” it does not include `Dockerfile.verify.rust` or `Dockerfile.verify.generic`.\n    14в†’\n    15в†’```bash\n    16в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'ls -la /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/templates/'\n    17в†’```\n    18в†’\n    19в†’```output\n    20в†’total 12\n    21в†’drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Mar 23 07:20 .\n    22в†’drwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Mar 23 07:20 ..\n    23в†’-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1065 Mar 23 07:20 Dockerfile.verify\n    24в†’```\n    25в†’\n    26в†’```bash\n    27в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/package.json | grep -A10 \"\\\"files\\\"\"'\n    28в†’```\n    29в†’\n    30в†’```output\n    31в†’\"files\": [\n    32в†’    \"dist\",\n    33в†’    \"bin\",\n    34в†’    \"patches\",\n    35в†’    \"templates/Dockerfile.verify\",\n    36в†’    \"ralph/**/*.sh\",\n    37в†’    \"ralph/AGENTS.md\"\n    38в†’  ],\n    39в†’```\n    40в†’\n    41в†’```bash\n    42в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'find / -name \"Dockerfile.verify.rust\" 2>/dev/null'\n    43в†’```\n    44в†’\n    45в†’```output\n    46в†’(no output вЂ” file does not exist anywhere in container)\n    47в†’```\n    48в†’\n    49в†’**Root cause:** `package.json` `files` array does not include `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`. The template was created in source but never added to the npm package manifest. The code in the bundle references `Dockerfile.verify.rust` (via `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS`), but `resolveDockerfileTemplate()` will throw at runtime because the file doesn't exist in the package's `templates/` directory.\n    50в†’\n    51в†’**Evidence that the template code references exist in the bundle:**\n    52в†’\n    53в†’```bash\n    54в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -o \"Dockerfile\\.verify\\.[a-z]*\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js | sort -u'\n    55в†’```\n    56в†’\n    57в†’```output\n    58в†’Dockerfile.verify.generic\n    59в†’Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    60в†’```\n    61в†’\n    62в†’```bash\n    63в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -c \"rust:1.82\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n    64в†’```\n    65в†’\n    66в†’```output\n    67в†’1\n    68в†’```\n    69в†’\n    70в†’```bash\n    71в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -c \"cargo-tarpaulin\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n    72в†’```\n    73в†’\n    74в†’```output\n    75в†’7\n    76в†’```\n    77в†’\n    78в†’The `rust:1.82-slim` base image reference exists in the bundle but belongs to the deployment `rustTemplate()` function (story 8-5), not the verification Dockerfile. Cannot verify the verification template content (base image, Semgrep, Node.js, showboat, cargo-tarpaulin, curl, jq) because the file is not shipped.\n    79в†’\n    80в†’---\n    81в†’\n    82в†’## AC2: OTLP environment variables in Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    83в†’\n    84в†’**Status: [FAIL]**\n    85в†’\n    86в†’Cannot verify OTLP env vars in the Rust verification Dockerfile because the file is not shipped in the package (see AC1). The existing `Dockerfile.verify` has the correct OTLP vars:\n    87в†’\n    88в†’```bash\n    89в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep \"OTEL_\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/templates/Dockerfile.verify'\n    90в†’```\n    91в†’\n    92в†’```output\n    93в†’ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318\n    94в†’ENV OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=codeharness-verify\n    95в†’ENV OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER=otlp\n    96в†’ENV OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER=otlp\n    97в†’ENV OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER=otlp\n    98в†’```\n    99в†’\n   100в†’But the Rust variant file does not exist to inspect.\n   101в†’\n   102в†’---\n   103в†’\n   104в†’## AC3: detectProjectType returns 'rust' for Rust projects\n   105в†’\n   106в†’**Status: [PASS]**\n   107в†’\n   108в†’```bash\n   109в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/test-rust-project && echo \"[package]\\nname = \\\"test\\\"\\nversion = \\\"0.1.0\\\"\" > /tmp/test-rust-project/Cargo.toml && cd /tmp/test-rust-project && codeharness init --json 2>&1'\n   110в†’```\n   111в†’\n   112в†’```output\n   113в†’{\"status\":\"fail\",\"stack\":\"rust\",\"enforcement\":{\"frontend\":true,\"database\":true,\"api\":true},\"documentation\":{\"agents_md\":\"skipped\",\"docs_scaffold\":\"skipped\",\"readme\":\"skipped\"},\"app_type\":\"generic\",\"dockerfile\":{\"generated\":true,\"stack\":\"rust\"},\"error\":\"Docker not installed\",\"docker\":{\"compose_file\":\"\",\"stack_running\":false,\"services\":[],\"ports\":{\"logs\":9428,\"metrics\":8428,\"traces\":16686,\"otel_grpc\":4317,\"otel_http\":4318}}}\n   114в†’```\n   115в†’\n   116в†’The JSON output shows `\"stack\":\"rust\"` вЂ” Rust project detection works correctly. The `\"error\":\"Docker not installed\"` is expected (no Docker-in-Docker).\n   117в†’\n   118в†’**Bundle evidence:**\n   119в†’\n   120в†’```bash\n   121в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -A8 \"function detectProjectType\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n   122в†’```\n   123в†’\n   124в†’```output\n   125в†’function detectProjectType(projectDir) {\n   126в†’  const stack = detectStack(projectDir);\n   127в†’  if (stack === \"nodejs\") return \"nodejs\";\n   128в†’  if (stack === \"python\") return \"python\";\n   129в†’  if (stack === \"rust\") return \"rust\";\n   130в†’  if (existsSync26(join23(projectDir, \".claude-plugin\", \"plugin.json\"))) return \"plugin\";\n   131в†’  return \"generic\";\n   132в†’}\n   133в†’```\n   134в†’\n   135в†’---\n   136в†’\n   137в†’## AC4: buildVerifyImage uses Dockerfile.verify.rust for Rust projects\n   138в†’\n   139в†’**Status: [PASS] (code-verified, runtime blocked by missing template file)**\n   140в†’\n   141в†’The bundle shows Rust projects are routed to `buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5)` which calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, \"rust\")` which maps to `Dockerfile.verify.rust`. The code path is correct but will fail at runtime because the template file is not shipped (AC1 failure).\n   142в†’\n   143в†’```bash\n   144в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'sed -n \"7385,7395p\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n   145в†’```\n   146в†’\n   147в†’```output\n   148в†’  if (projectType === \"nodejs\") {\n   149в†’    buildNodeImage(projectDir);\n   150в†’  } else if (projectType === \"python\") {\n   151в†’    buildPythonImage(projectDir);\n   152в†’  } else if (projectType === \"rust\") {\n   153в†’    buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5);\n   154в†’  } else if (projectType === \"plugin\") {\n   155в†’    buildPluginImage(projectDir);\n   156в†’  } else {\n   157в†’    buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"generic\");\n   158в†’  }\n   159в†’```\n   160в†’\n   161в†’---\n   162в†’\n   163в†’## AC5: resolveDockerfileTemplate resolves Dockerfile.verify.rust for variant 'rust'\n   164в†’\n   165в†’**Status: [PASS] (code-verified, runtime will throw due to missing file)**\n   166в†’\n   167в†’```bash\n   168в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -A10 \"var DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n   169в†’```\n   170в†’\n   171в†’```output\n   172в†’var DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS = {\n   173в†’  generic: \"Dockerfile.verify.generic\",\n   174в†’  rust: \"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"\n   175в†’};\n   176в†’function resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, variant) {\n   177в†’  const filename = (variant && DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS[variant]) ?? \"Dockerfile.verify\";\n   178в†’  const local = join23(projectDir, \"templates\", filename);\n   179в†’  if (existsSync26(local)) return local;\n   180в†’  const pkgDir = new URL(\"../../\", import.meta.url).pathname;\n   181в†’  const pkg = join23(pkgDir, \"templates\", filename);\n   182в†’```\n   183в†’\n   184в†’The `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` map correctly maps `\"rust\"` to `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"`. The function logic resolves variants correctly.\n   185в†’\n   186в†’---\n   187в†’\n   188в†’## AC6: ProjectType includes 'rust'\n   189в†’\n   190в†’**Status: [PASS]**\n   191в†’\n   192в†’The bundle includes `\"rust\"` as a valid project type in all relevant code paths:\n   193в†’\n   194в†’```bash\n   195в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep \"rust\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js | grep -c \"projectType\\|ProjectType\\|detectProjectType\"'\n   196в†’```\n   197в†’\n   198в†’```output\n   199в†’3\n   200в†’```\n   201в†’\n   202в†’Evidence from the `detectProjectType` function returning `\"rust\"` (see AC3) and `buildVerifyImage` routing `\"rust\"` (see AC4) confirms `'rust'` is a valid project type in the type union.\n   203в†’\n   204в†’---\n   205в†’\n   206в†’## AC7: codeharness init on Rust project builds Rust-specific verification image\n   207в†’\n   208в†’**Status: [FAIL]**\n   209в†’\n   210в†’Two blockers:\n   211в†’1. Docker is not available inside the container (no Docker-in-Docker), so `buildVerifyImage` cannot execute.\n   212в†’2. Even if Docker were available, the build would fail because `Dockerfile.verify.rust` is not shipped in the npm package (AC1 failure).\n   213в†’\n   214в†’```bash\n   215в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-rust-project && codeharness verify-env build --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n   216в†’```\n   217в†’\n   218в†’```output\n   219в†’{\"status\":\"fail\",\"message\":\"Docker is not available. Install Docker and ensure the daemon is running.\"}\n   220в†’EXIT:1\n   221в†’```\n   222в†’\n   223в†’Detection works (AC3 passes), routing code is correct (AC4/AC5 pass), but end-to-end integration cannot be verified.\n   224в†’\n   225в†’---\n   226в†’\n   227в†’## AC8: npm test passes with zero regressions\n   228в†’\n   229в†’**Status: [ESCALATE]**\n   230в†’\n   231в†’No source code is available in the container (`/workspace` is empty). Cannot run `npm test`.\n   232в†’\n   233в†’```bash\n   234в†’docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'ls /workspace/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n   235в†’```\n   236в†’\n   237в†’```output\n   238в†’EXIT:0\n   239в†’```\n   240в†’\n   241в†’This AC requires source code and a test runner, which are not available in the black-box verification container by design. The dev agent's completion notes state \"2998 tests pass, zero regressions.\"\n   242в†’\n   243в†’---\n   244в†’\n   245в†’## Summary\n   246в†’\n   247в†’| AC | Status | Notes |\n   248в†’|----|--------|-------|\n   249в†’| AC1 | **FAIL** | `Dockerfile.verify.rust` not shipped in npm package (`package.json` `files` missing entry) |\n   250в†’| AC2 | **FAIL** | Cannot inspect OTLP vars вЂ” template file not shipped |\n   251в†’| AC3 | **PASS** | `codeharness init --json` returns `\"stack\":\"rust\"` for Cargo.toml project |\n   252в†’| AC4 | **PASS** | Bundle routes `rust` в†’ `buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5)` |\n   253в†’| AC5 | **PASS** | `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` maps `\"rust\"` в†’ `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` |\n   254в†’| AC6 | **PASS** | `\"rust\"` is a valid project type in all code paths |\n   255в†’| AC7 | **FAIL** | No Docker-in-Docker + template file not shipped |\n   256в†’| AC8 | **ESCALATE** | No source code in container; cannot run tests |\n   257в†’\n   258в†’### Critical Bug Found\n   259в†’\n   260в†’**`package.json` `files` field does not include `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`** (or `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`). The template file exists in source but is not packaged. At runtime, `resolveDockerfileTemplate(\"rust\")` will throw: `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust not found. Ensure templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust exists.\"` This makes the Rust verification pipeline non-functional despite correct code logic.\n   261в†’\n   262в†’**Fix required:** Add `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` (and `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic\"`) to the `files` array in `package.json`.\n   263в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"62ae53bd-1e5a-46ad-b29f-92be12563e67","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:24:48.135Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile-proof.md","content":"# Story 8.6: Rust Verification Dockerfile вЂ” Verification Proof\n\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n**Date:** 2026-03-23\n**Container:** codeharness-verify (codeharness v0.23.1)\n\n---\n\n## AC1: Dockerfile.verify.rust template content\n\n**Status: [FAIL]**\n\nThe `Dockerfile.verify.rust` template file is **not shipped** in the npm package. The `package.json` `files` field only includes `templates/Dockerfile.verify` вЂ” it does not include `Dockerfile.verify.rust` or `Dockerfile.verify.generic`.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'ls -la /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/templates/'\n```\n\n```output\ntotal 12\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Mar 23 07:20 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Mar 23 07:20 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1065 Mar 23 07:20 Dockerfile.verify\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/package.json | grep -A10 \"\\\"files\\\"\"'\n```\n\n```output\n\"files\": [\n    \"dist\",\n    \"bin\",\n    \"patches\",\n    \"templates/Dockerfile.verify\",\n    \"ralph/**/*.sh\",\n    \"ralph/AGENTS.md\"\n  ],\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'find / -name \"Dockerfile.verify.rust\" 2>/dev/null'\n```\n\n```output\n(no output вЂ” file does not exist anywhere in container)\n```\n\n**Root cause:** `package.json` `files` array does not include `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`. The template was created in source but never added to the npm package manifest. The code in the bundle references `Dockerfile.verify.rust` (via `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS`), but `resolveDockerfileTemplate()` will throw at runtime because the file doesn't exist in the package's `templates/` directory.\n\n**Evidence that the template code references exist in the bundle:**\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -o \"Dockerfile\\.verify\\.[a-z]*\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js | sort -u'\n```\n\n```output\nDockerfile.verify.generic\nDockerfile.verify.rust\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -c \"rust:1.82\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\n1\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -c \"cargo-tarpaulin\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\n7\n```\n\nThe `rust:1.82-slim` base image reference exists in the bundle but belongs to the deployment `rustTemplate()` function (story 8-5), not the verification Dockerfile. Cannot verify the verification template content (base image, Semgrep, Node.js, showboat, cargo-tarpaulin, curl, jq) because the file is not shipped.\n\n---\n\n## AC2: OTLP environment variables in Dockerfile.verify.rust\n\n**Status: [FAIL]**\n\nCannot verify OTLP env vars in the Rust verification Dockerfile because the file is not shipped in the package (see AC1). The existing `Dockerfile.verify` has the correct OTLP vars:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep \"OTEL_\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/templates/Dockerfile.verify'\n```\n\n```output\nENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318\nENV OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=codeharness-verify\nENV OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER=otlp\nENV OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER=otlp\nENV OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER=otlp\n```\n\nBut the Rust variant file does not exist to inspect.\n\n---\n\n## AC3: detectProjectType returns 'rust' for Rust projects\n\n**Status: [PASS]**\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/test-rust-project && echo \"[package]\\nname = \\\"test\\\"\\nversion = \\\"0.1.0\\\"\" > /tmp/test-rust-project/Cargo.toml && cd /tmp/test-rust-project && codeharness init --json 2>&1'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"fail\",\"stack\":\"rust\",\"enforcement\":{\"frontend\":true,\"database\":true,\"api\":true},\"documentation\":{\"agents_md\":\"skipped\",\"docs_scaffold\":\"skipped\",\"readme\":\"skipped\"},\"app_type\":\"generic\",\"dockerfile\":{\"generated\":true,\"stack\":\"rust\"},\"error\":\"Docker not installed\",\"docker\":{\"compose_file\":\"\",\"stack_running\":false,\"services\":[],\"ports\":{\"logs\":9428,\"metrics\":8428,\"traces\":16686,\"otel_grpc\":4317,\"otel_http\":4318}}}\n```\n\nThe JSON output shows `\"stack\":\"rust\"` вЂ” Rust project detection works correctly. The `\"error\":\"Docker not installed\"` is expected (no Docker-in-Docker).\n\n**Bundle evidence:**\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -A8 \"function detectProjectType\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\nfunction detectProjectType(projectDir) {\n  const stack = detectStack(projectDir);\n  if (stack === \"nodejs\") return \"nodejs\";\n  if (stack === \"python\") return \"python\";\n  if (stack === \"rust\") return \"rust\";\n  if (existsSync26(join23(projectDir, \".claude-plugin\", \"plugin.json\"))) return \"plugin\";\n  return \"generic\";\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC4: buildVerifyImage uses Dockerfile.verify.rust for Rust projects\n\n**Status: [PASS] (code-verified, runtime blocked by missing template file)**\n\nThe bundle shows Rust projects are routed to `buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5)` which calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, \"rust\")` which maps to `Dockerfile.verify.rust`. The code path is correct but will fail at runtime because the template file is not shipped (AC1 failure).\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'sed -n \"7385,7395p\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\n  if (projectType === \"nodejs\") {\n    buildNodeImage(projectDir);\n  } else if (projectType === \"python\") {\n    buildPythonImage(projectDir);\n  } else if (projectType === \"rust\") {\n    buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5);\n  } else if (projectType === \"plugin\") {\n    buildPluginImage(projectDir);\n  } else {\n    buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"generic\");\n  }\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC5: resolveDockerfileTemplate resolves Dockerfile.verify.rust for variant 'rust'\n\n**Status: [PASS] (code-verified, runtime will throw due to missing file)**\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -A10 \"var DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\nvar DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS = {\n  generic: \"Dockerfile.verify.generic\",\n  rust: \"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"\n};\nfunction resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, variant) {\n  const filename = (variant && DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS[variant]) ?? \"Dockerfile.verify\";\n  const local = join23(projectDir, \"templates\", filename);\n  if (existsSync26(local)) return local;\n  const pkgDir = new URL(\"../../\", import.meta.url).pathname;\n  const pkg = join23(pkgDir, \"templates\", filename);\n```\n\nThe `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` map correctly maps `\"rust\"` to `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"`. The function logic resolves variants correctly.\n\n---\n\n## AC6: ProjectType includes 'rust'\n\n**Status: [PASS]**\n\nThe bundle includes `\"rust\"` as a valid project type in all relevant code paths:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep \"rust\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js | grep -c \"projectType\\|ProjectType\\|detectProjectType\"'\n```\n\n```output\n3\n```\n\nEvidence from the `detectProjectType` function returning `\"rust\"` (see AC3) and `buildVerifyImage` routing `\"rust\"` (see AC4) confirms `'rust'` is a valid project type in the type union.\n\n---\n\n## AC7: codeharness init on Rust project builds Rust-specific verification image\n\n**Status: [FAIL]**\n\nTwo blockers:\n1. Docker is not available inside the container (no Docker-in-Docker), so `buildVerifyImage` cannot execute.\n2. Even if Docker were available, the build would fail because `Dockerfile.verify.rust` is not shipped in the npm package (AC1 failure).\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-rust-project && codeharness verify-env build --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"fail\",\"message\":\"Docker is not available. Install Docker and ensure the daemon is running.\"}\nEXIT:1\n```\n\nDetection works (AC3 passes), routing code is correct (AC4/AC5 pass), but end-to-end integration cannot be verified.\n\n---\n\n## AC8: npm test passes with zero regressions\n\n**Status: [ESCALATE]**\n\nNo source code is available in the container (`/workspace` is empty). Cannot run `npm test`.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'ls /workspace/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\nEXIT:0\n```\n\nThis AC requires source code and a test runner, which are not available in the black-box verification container by design. The dev agent's completion notes state \"2998 tests pass, zero regressions.\"\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Status | Notes |\n|----|--------|-------|\n| AC1 | **FAIL** | `Dockerfile.verify.rust` not shipped in npm package (`package.json` `files` missing entry) |\n| AC2 | **FAIL** | Cannot inspect OTLP vars вЂ” template file not shipped |\n| AC3 | **PASS** | `codeharness init --json` returns `\"stack\":\"rust\"` for Cargo.toml project |\n| AC4 | **PASS** | Bundle routes `rust` в†’ `buildSimpleImage(projectDir, \"rust\", 3e5)` |\n| AC5 | **PASS** | `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` maps `\"rust\"` в†’ `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` |\n| AC6 | **PASS** | `\"rust\"` is a valid project type in all code paths |\n| AC7 | **FAIL** | No Docker-in-Docker + template file not shipped |\n| AC8 | **ESCALATE** | No source code in container; cannot run tests |\n\n### Critical Bug Found\n\n**`package.json` `files` field does not include `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust`** (or `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`). The template file exists in source but is not packaged. At runtime, `resolveDockerfileTemplate(\"rust\")` will throw: `\"Dockerfile.verify.rust not found. Ensure templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust exists.\"` This makes the Rust verification pipeline non-functional despite correct code logic.\n\n**Fix required:** Add `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\"` (and `\"templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic\"`) to the `files` array in `package.json`.\n","numLines":263,"startLine":1,"totalLines":263}}}
