{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0136WeFAG5MCk1qrsEQgBjTK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Session Issues Log вЂ” 2026-03-23\n     2в†’\n     3в†’### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust вЂ” verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n     4в†’\n     5в†’- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n     6в†’- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n     7в†’- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n     8в†’- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file вЂ” likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n     9в†’\n    10в†’### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection вЂ” create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n    11в†’\n    12в†’- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n    13в†’- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n    14в†’- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path вЂ” existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n    15в†’\n    16в†’### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection вЂ” dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n    17в†’\n    18в†’- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround вЂ” adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n    19в†’- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters вЂ” fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n    20в†’- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n    21в†’\n    22в†’### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection вЂ” code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n    23в†’\n    24в†’- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n    25в†’- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` вЂ” if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n    26в†’- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects вЂ” unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n    27в†’- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) вЂ” caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n    28в†’- **Time constraint:** Verification not started вЂ” insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n    29в†’\n    30в†’### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection вЂ” verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)\n    31в†’\n    32в†’- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\n    33в†’- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\n    34в†’- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected вЂ” container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\n    35в†’- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.\n    36в†’\n    37в†’### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry вЂ” create-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)\n    38в†’\n    39в†’- **Unconditional dependency registry:** Adding `cargo-tarpaulin` means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully (`critical: false`) but is noisy. Stack-conditional filtering would be a separate story.\n    40в†’- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** The file already existed as a skeleton from sprint planning. Overwritten with comprehensive story as expected.\n    41в†’- **Risk: deps-install.test.ts mock registry:** Consumer test mocks `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with hardcoded single-entry array. Mock isolates consumer from registry changes вЂ” no update needed there.\n    42в†’\n    43в†’### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry вЂ” dev-story (2026-03-23T09:28Z)\n    44в†’\n    45в†’- **Pre-existing test failures:** 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite вЂ” test isolation issue, not related to this story.\n    46в†’- **Unconditional registry design acknowledged:** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on non-Rust projects. `critical: false` handles graceful failure. Stack-conditional filtering deferred.\n    47в†’\n    48в†’### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry вЂ” code-review (2026-03-23T09:35Z)\n    49в†’\n    50в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale вЂ” deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list.\n    51в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Story File List empty вЂ” no files documented in Dev Agent Record.\n    52в†’- **LOW (not fixed):** Fragile catch-all mock in installAllDependencies tests вЂ” implicitly handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough rather than explicit mock branch.\n    53в†’- Coverage: 97% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n    54в†’\n    55в†’### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry вЂ” verify (2026-03-23T09:42Z)\n    56в†’\n    57в†’- All 5 ACs passed black-box verification.\n    58в†’- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed вЂ” recurring issue across sessions.\n    59в†’- **Showboat not installed warning** during `codeharness verify` вЂ” non-blocking but means no re-verification via showboat.\n    60в†’- No observability gaps reported by verifier for this story.\n    61в†’\n    62в†’### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template вЂ” create-story (2026-03-23T10:41Z)\n    63в†’\n    64в†’- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** Stub story file already existed from earlier epic planning. Overwritten with comprehensive version.\n    65в†’- **Workflow naming mismatch:** workflow.md referenced in skill was actually workflow.yaml вЂ” minor.\n    66в†’- **Risk: checkNoSourceCopy validator false positive:** The `COPY src/` pattern in the validator regex could false-match on Rust template's `COPY . .` builder stage. Story documents this prominently but dev agent could miss it.\n    67в†’- **Risk: AC7 integration-required:** Depends on `detectStack()` returning `'rust'` for real Rust project during `codeharness init`. Cannot verify purely via unit tests.\n    68в†’\n    69в†’### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template вЂ” dev-story (2026-03-23T10:45Z)\n    70в†’\n    71в†’- **Pre-existing test failure:** `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` line 261 fails (`migrateFromOldFormat` returns `success: false`). Unrelated to this story.\n    72в†’- **No workarounds applied.** Implementation follows existing patterns exactly.\n    73в†’- **34/34 dockerfile-template tests pass.** 2994/2995 full suite (1 pre-existing failure).\n    74в†’\n    75в†’### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template вЂ” verify (2026-03-23T10:57Z)\n    76в†’\n    77в†’- **Proof format issue:** AC3 and AC4 referenced AC2's Dockerfile output without their own `bash`+`output` code blocks. Proof validator counted them as \"pending\" (5/7). Fixed by adding per-AC grep evidence blocks.\n    78в†’- **Observability gap:** All 7 ACs showed no log events in VictoriaLogs. Recurring pattern вЂ” CLI commands don't emit telemetry in verify container.\n    79в†’- **Beads sync skipped:** `bd` binary not installed (recurring).\n    80в†’- **Showboat re-verification skipped:** showboat not installed (recurring).\n    81в†’\n    82в†’### 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template вЂ” code-review (2026-03-23T10:50Z)\n    83в†’\n    84в†’- **HIGH (fixed):** Missing showboat proof document вЂ” created with AC-by-AC evidence.\n    85в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale вЂ” omitted rust from dockerfile-template.ts entry.\n    86в†’- **MEDIUM (not fixed, design decision):** Rust template has no ENTRYPOINT/CMD вЂ” consistent with all other templates.\n    87в†’- **LOW (not fixed):** Hardcoded `rust:1.82-slim` will age. Users edit the template.\n    88в†’- **LOW (not fixed):** Error-path tests only exercise nodejs stack (code is stack-agnostic).\n    89в†’- Coverage: 97% overall, 100% for dockerfile-template.ts, all files above 80% floor.\n    90в†’\n    91в†’### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile вЂ” create-story (2026-03-23T11:10Z)\n    92в†’\n    93в†’- **Ambiguity: showboat installation in Rust image.** Epic says \"showboat\" but doesn't mention it's an npm package requiring Node.js. Prior draft incorrectly listed `pipx install showboat`. Story now documents Node.js dependency.\n    94в†’- **Risk: env.ts approaching 300-line limit.** File is 293 lines. Adding `buildRustImage()` puts it around ~308 lines.\n    95в†’- **Observation: prior draft existed.** Minimal draft (74 lines, 2 ACs) overwritten with comprehensive version (217 lines, 8 ACs, 8 tasks).\n    96в†’\n    97в†’### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile вЂ” dev-story (2026-03-23T11:17Z)\n    98в†’\n    99в†’- **Task 5.2 deviation:** Story specified copying Cargo.toml/Cargo.lock/src into build context. Dev Notes clarified this is a tools-only image (project mounted at runtime), so buildRustImage follows buildGenericImage pattern with Dockerfile-only context. Task marked complete despite deviation.\n   100в†’- **Build timeout:** buildRustImage uses 300s timeout (vs 120s for others) because cargo install cargo-tarpaulin compiles from source. Minor pattern deviation.\n   101в†’- **env.ts line count:** File grew from 293 to ~307 lines, slightly over 300-line soft limit.\n   102в†’\n   103в†’### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile вЂ” code-review (2026-03-23T11:24Z)\n   104в†’\n   105в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** NFR9 violation вЂ” env.ts was 307 lines (> 300 limit). Merged buildRustImage and buildGenericImage into buildSimpleImage helper. Now 299 lines.\n   106в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unreadable nested ternary in resolveDockerfileTemplate. Replaced with DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS lookup map.\n   107в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Stale comment in hash-skip section.\n   108в†’- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale вЂ” didn't document Rust as supported project type.\n   109в†’- **LOW (not fixed):** Tests cast 'rust' as ReturnType<typeof detectStack> unnecessarily.\n   110в†’- **Coverage gap:** No test for buildSimpleImage timeout parameter propagation (Rust 300s vs generic 120s).\n   111в†’- **Coverage gap:** AC7 integration test marked integration-required вЂ” needs Docker verification.\n   112в†’\n   113в†’### 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile вЂ” verify attempt 1 (2026-03-23T11:28Z)\n   114в†’\n   115в†’- **CRITICAL BUG FOUND:** package.json `files` array missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic`. Template files existed in source but not shipped in npm package. Fixed by adding entries to `files` array.\n   