{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VFtLJ8C6awrFzTuspZF9hj","type":"tool_result","content":"   700в†’\n   701в†’### Repeat\n   702в†’\n   703в†’- **Self-review before verification.** 14 bugs found across 5 stories this session. This is the single most effective quality measure. Never skip it.\n   704в†’- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` in real time.** Every subagent appended issues as encountered. This file made 4 retrospective addenda possible.\n   705в†’- **One story per iteration after the first.** Iterations 5 and 6 each completed a full story lifecycle in 15-20 minutes. This pacing works reliably.\n   706в†’- **Follow existing patterns for new stack support.** 8-5 had zero workarounds because it followed the established template pattern exactly.\n   707в†’\n   708в†’### Avoid\n   709в†’\n   710в†’- **Do not pack more than 1 story + retro into a 30-minute iteration.** Iteration 1 proved this. Budget 1 story per iteration, retro as a separate short iteration.\n   711в†’- **Do not defer `coverage.ts` split any further.** It has been flagged in 3 consecutive story reviews. Story 8-6 or 8-7 will add more Rust code to it. Split before continuing.\n   712в†’- **Do not ignore the state tracking desync.** Three files disagreeing on story status is not \"eventually consistent\" -- it is broken. Pick one source of truth and deprecate or automate the others.\n   713в†’\n   714в†’---\n   715в†’\n   716в†’## 6. Action Items\n   717в†’\n   718в†’### Fix Now (before next session)\n   719в†’\n   720в†’- [ ] Reconcile all three state files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) -- set 8-5 to `done`, sprint done count to 30\n   721в†’- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers\n   722в†’\n   723в†’### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   724в†’\n   725в†’- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into Rust/Node/Python parser modules. 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit. Branch coverage below floor. Blocking further growth.\n   726в†’- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align detection with `codeharness-shared-*`. Wastes time every session since Epic 7.\n   727в†’- [ ] **Add stack-conditional filtering to dependency registry** -- `cargo-tarpaulin` should only install for Rust projects.\n   728в†’- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence.\n   729в†’- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into single utility.\n   730в†’- [ ] **Expose `runCommand`/`reportFormat` in `codeharness coverage --json`** -- CLI gap forces verification to replicate internal logic.\n   731в†’- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** -- observability gap.\n   732в†’- [ ] **Fix 4 pre-existing test isolation failures** in `state.test.ts`.\n   733в†’- [ ] **Fix 1 pre-existing failure** in `migration.test.ts`.\n   734в†’\n   735в†’### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   736в†’\n   737в†’- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics)\n   738в†’- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   739в†’- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   740в†’- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates\n   741в†’- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number values\n   742в†’- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing\n   743в†’- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing\n   744в†’- [ ] Install `bd` binary so beads sync can function\n   745в†’- [ ] Install showboat for re-verification capability\n   746в†’- [ ] Add ENTRYPOINT/CMD to Rust Dockerfile template (or document why it is omitted)\n   747в†’- [ ] Add error-path tests for non-nodejs stacks in dockerfile-template\n   748в†’\n   749в†’---\n   750в†’\n   751в†’## Session Metrics (Final -- Addendum 4)\n   752в†’\n   753в†’| Metric | Value |\n   754в†’|--------|-------|\n   755в†’| Stories completed | 5 (8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4, 8-5) |\n   756в†’| Stories failed | 0 |\n   757в†’| Bugs found pre-verification | 14 (5 HIGH, 9 MEDIUM) |\n   758в†’| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM, 7 LOW (accepted) |\n   759в†’| Ralph iterations | 6 |\n   760в†’| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   761в†’| Commits | 5 |\n   762в†’| Total test count | 2994+ passing (2995 total, 1 pre-existing failure) |\n   763в†’| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 30/34 (88% done) |\n   764в†’| Epics completed this session | 2 full (Epic 8.1, 8.2) + 1 partial (Epic 8.3: 1/2 stories) |\n   765в†’| Remaining backlog | 4 stories (8-6, 8-7, 8-8, 8-9 in Epic 8.3-8.5) |\n   766в†’| Recurring issues unfixed | 8 (Docker naming, sync, state desync, test isolation, coverage.ts size, migration test, bd, showboat) |\n   767в†’| Session velocity | ~5 stories / ~112 min = 1 story per ~22 min avg |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mj2gGGRiwgbDummKyN8nVt","session_id":"51b9d113-d480-4846-9e18-693f5f89566d","uuid":"bca02a8f-5d95-42fd-a902-198dc2837849","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:31:23.995Z"}
